lead_paragraph: The United States played a key role in the intense lobbying that saw Gianni Infantino elected FIFA president on Friday, beating Sheikh Salman Bin Ebrahim Al Khalifa, as the old political allegiances at world football's governing body collapsed.

headline.print_headline: Infantino Triumphs With American Help as FIFA Blocks Break Down
